                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "If there was no real difference, making languages visual wouldn't do anything. They would be adopted at the same rate, by the same people, with the same amount of success. Evidence categorically shows otherwise. Visual language seem pointless only to people suffering the curse of expertise. They are not FOR people who have already struggled through learning how to use parenthesis for containment. They are for people for whom that struggle and others like it are not obviously worth going through. They are curb cuts to allow people in wheelchairs to cross roads, and people who can walk saying they are pointless is distasteful."
                            }
